item.dc:creator: @pplsuqbawlz pplsuqbawlz
item.description:
@pplsuqbawlz wrote:

Lol incredibly, the new cache is multi-layer collapsed.

it goes something like:

[code]
public byte[] getFile(int index) {
anInt1409++;
//noinspection SynchronizeOnNonFinalField
synchronized (filecache) {
try {
if ((long) (index * 6 + 6) > fileindex.getLength())
return null;

            fileindex.seek((long) (index * 6));
            fileindex.read(BUFFER, 0, 6);

            int len = ((BUFFER[0] & 0xff) << 16) + ((BUFFER[1] & 0xff) << 8) + (BUFFER[2] & 0xff);
            int pos = ((BUFFER[3] & 0xff) << 16) + ((BUFFER[4] & 0xff) << 8) + (BUFFER[5] & 0xff);

            if (len < 0 || len > length)
                return null;

            if (pos <= 0 || (long) pos > filecache.getLength() / 520L)
                return null;

            int read = 0;
            int parity = 0;
            byte[] bytes = new byte[len];

            while (len > read) {
                if (pos == 0)
                    return null;

                filecache.seek((long) (pos * 520));

                int size = len - read;

                if (size > 512)
                    size = 512;

                filecache.read(BUFFER, 0, size + 8);

                int r_index = ((BUFFER[0] & 0xff) << 8) + (BUFFER[1] & 0xff);
                int r_parity = ((BUFFER[2] & 0xff) << 8) + (BUFFER[3] & 0xff);
                int r_position = ((BUFFER[4] & 0xff) << 16) + ((BUFFER[5] & 0xff) << 8) + (BUFFER[6] & 0xff);
                int r_type = BUFFER[7] & 0xff;

                if (index != r_index || parity != r_parity || type != r_type)
                    return null;

                if (r_position < 0 || filecache.getLength() / 520L < (long) r_position)
                    return null;

                for (int i = 0; i < size; i++)
                    bytes[read++] = BUFFER[i + 8];

                parity++;
                pos = r_position;
            }

            return bytes;
        } catch (IOException ioexception) {
            return null;
        }
    }
}[/code]
